    Date: Wednesday, 13 August 1986  15:05-EDT
    From: "Larry Peterson" &lt;llp@arizona.edu&gt;

    A new topic: I see a need for a human contact point for
    each domain; a "distributed" incarnation of the hostmaster.
    I suggest "domainmaster", which is defined in every domain
    and bound to someone's mailbox. For example, I should be able
    to report trouble I'm having resolving the name vax1.ox.ac.uk
    to domainmaster.uk, domainmaster.ac.uk, etc. I also have no
    problem with domainmaster@domain, if the domain is bound to a host.

I thought that's what the bug-address field of the SOA RR was for.
(The RNAME field in the description of the SOA RR on page 65 of
RFC883, that is.)

--Rob

